############################
#     1. Introduction      #
############################

 Name: CAE SPlayer Plugin v1.0.0
 Description: Stream player with extensive syncronization capabilities

 Lincensing         -> LICENSE
 History            -> NEWS
 
 To clone the repository with all the submodules use 
   git clone --recursive git://github.com/Cae-Engineering/splayer

############################
#       2. Libraries       #
############################

 Firebreath 
 FFmpeg

############################
#     3. Dependencies      #
############################ 

Mac OS X:
 cmake 
 xcode

Windows
 minGW (/w MSYS Basic System and MinGW Developer ToolKit)
 cmake (add CMake to the system PATH)
 patch (included in git)
 Windows Driver Kit Version 7.1.0 (Full Development Environment)

############################
#        4. Build          #
############################

Mac OS X:
  1, ./mac.sh
  2, Open 'build/FireBreath.xcodeproj' with XCode
  3, Set the active scheme to Splayer
  4, Compile

Windows (to be fixed):
  1, copy the cloned splayer to ..msys/../home
  2, open a minGW shell and enter the copied splayer folder
  3, apply patch of FFmpeg (patch -p0 < FFmpeg.patch, might need a Git Shell)
  4, add the following to FFmpeg\libavformat\tcp.c
     #ifndef MSG_NOSIGNAL
     #define MSG_NOSIGNAL 0
     #endif
  5, make -C libffmpeg (be extremely patient)
  6, run genwinlib.cmd (convert *.a to *.obj)
  7, clone Firebreath and checkout to 1.7.0 into msys/../home/splayer folder
  8, change genw.cmd in order to have a project for VS 2012 ("Firebreath\prep2012.cmd" projects build)
  9, run genw.cmd

